<h2><a name="reset" id="reset">reset</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;bitset&gt;</span>
    bitset<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>N<span class="sy0">&gt;&amp;</span> reset<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    bitset<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>N<span class="sy0">&gt;&amp;</span> reset<span class="br0">&#40;</span> size_t pos <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>
The reset() function clears all of the bits in the bitset, and returns the
bitset. If pos is specified, then only the bit at position pos is cleared.
</p>

</div>
